            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>This year, Allen is looking to be a stabilizing force for another young team, the role Quinn Cook played on the national title-winning team his freshman year.&nbsp;</p>
<p>“I just tried to stay out of the way of the upperclassmen," Allen <a href="https://www.theplayerstribune.com/grayson-allen-duke-basketball/" target="_blank">wrote</a> in the Players Tribune piece. "Quinn Cook wasn’t having any of that. Quinn was the oldest guy on the team. He was our captain—our heart and soul. Quinn’s the type of person who, when he’s talking everybody in the room listens.”&nbsp;</p>
<p>Grayson Allen came back because he had some growing up to do. So far, he looks like the senior leader that could be the difference come March.&nbsp;</p>
<p><em>Check in tomorrow to see what story comes in at No. 3 on our list.&nbsp;</em></p>
